    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-03-01T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-03-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="551"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d551">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 738.3915/96.]</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">American Minister to Haiti</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Extract.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-03-01">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 1, 1912</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>In regard to your No. 1019; you will urgently counsel the Minister for Foreign
                    Affairs against further delay of the issue of full powers in accordance with the
                    Department’s January 15. The meeting of the plenipotentiaries must not be
                    delayed by any question concerning the status quo line.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
